SIMPLE: twig
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twig
<hw>Twig</hw> <pr>(tw⟦icr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Twigged</conjf> <pr>(tw⟦icr⟧gd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Twigging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Tweak</er>.]</ety> <def>To twitch; to pull; to tweak.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twig
<hw>Twig</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Gael. <ets>tuig</ets>, or Ir.
<ets>tuigim</ets> I understand.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To understand the meaning of; to comprehend; as, do
you <xex>twig</xex> me?</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Marryat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To observe slyly; also, to perceive; to
discover.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Now <xex>twig</xex> him; now mind him.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Foote.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if he were looking right into your eyes and <qex>twigged</qex>
something there which you had half a mind to conceal.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twig
<hw>Twig</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>twig</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>twijg</ets>, OHG. <ets>zw⟦imac⟧g</ets>, <ets>zw⟦imac⟧</ets>, G.
<ets>zweig</ets>, and probably to E. <ets>two</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small
shoot or branch of a tree or other plant, of no definite length or
size.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Britons had boats made of willow <qex>twigs</qex>, covered on
the outside with hides.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Twig borer</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any one of
several species of small beetles which bore into twigs of shrubs and
trees, as the apple-tree <ex>twig borer</ex> (<spn>Amphicerus
bicaudatus</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>Twig girdler</b></col>.
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See <er>Girdler</er>, 3.</cd> -- <col><b>Twig
rush</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>any rushlike plant of the genus
<gen>Cladium</gen> having hard, and sometimes prickly-edged, leaves or
stalks. See <cref>Saw grass</cref>, under <er>Saw</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Twig
<hw>Twig</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To beat with twigs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twiggen</ent>⟦br⟧
